{
  "_about": "Golden Krill GK1 wire-codec conformance vectors. The single anti-drift contract for every port (Dart, TS, C#, Swift, Kotlin) and the Python backend. Each case pins a known input JSON string to its exact GK1 blob and its decoded struct. A port passes if, for every case: decode(gk1) == json (byte-exact) AND encode(json) == gk1 (byte-exact). GENERATED by conformance/generate_vectors.py from golden-krill/web/apps/catalog/gk1.py; do not hand-edit. GK1 is frozen/eternal (add GK2 for new layouts, never repurpose GK1).",
  "codec": {
    "tag": "GK1.",
    "key_utf8": "pink-rorqual//golden-krill//v1",
    "algorithm": "blob = \"GK1.\" + base64url( XOR(utf8(json), key) ). The key is cycled over the bytes; XOR is its own inverse (same routine encodes and decodes). base64url INCLUDES '=' padding. Decode also passes raw JSON through (a leading '{' or '[') for dev/test."
  },
